A man, believed to be in his 30s was killed and eight
others injured on Friday morning following a collision between a taxi and
modified motorbike on White Road in Grange, on the outskirts of
Pietermaritzburg.ER24 paramedics arrived on the scene shortly after 08:00
to find the taxi on the side of the road while the motorbike was found some
distance away on the right-hand side of the road."Upon closer inspection, paramedics discovered the
body of a man in his 30s, believed to be the driver of the motorbike, lying
behind the taxi. Unfortunately, the man had already succumbed to his injuries.
